  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/79211967" />
    <a title="valee" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2320890-valee"><img alt="valee" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1443365004p2/2320890.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/79211967?book_show_action=true">Nov 28, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="valee" class="user" itemprop="url" name="valee" href="/user/show/2320890-valee">valee</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2320890-valee?shelf=average-pnr-romance">average-pnr-romance</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer79211967" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1064844275336966908">I&apos;m totally disappointed with Nora Roberts. I really wanted to like her but I couldn&apos;t. I thought there must be a reason for why she is so famous, but this series was not a good one. I only enjoyed the first book in the series, the rest were not very good.<br/><br/>I really hated the ghost story, I really didn&apos;t care for it, it was boring. I did enjoy the first book because the ghost was a secondary element in it, but in the 2nd and 3rd book it was mentioned too much.<br/><br/>And about the romance, it never did de</span>
  <span id="freeText1064844275336966908" style="display:none">I'm totally disappointed with Nora Roberts. I really wanted to like her but I couldn't. I thought there must be a reason for why she is so famous, but this series was not a good one. I only enjoyed the first book in the series, the rest were not very good.<br /><br />I really hated the ghost story, I really didn't care for it, it was boring. I did enjoy the first book because the ghost was a secondary element in it, but in the 2nd and 3rd book it was mentioned too much.<br /><br />And about the romance, it never did develop correctly, I felt most of the time like something was missing. The characters talked in a way which did not let you get to know them. All the time I felt like actions were taking place but feeling and emotions were left as secondary elements, you never get to know the characters. I really wanted to get finished with this series. I wouldn't recommend it. I mean, it had some good parts, just not good enough. With all the amazing books that are out there I would not loose my time with this one.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1064844275336966908" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


