  <span id="freeText15819483193392309054" style="display:none"><b>
  <u>2020</u>
</b><br />The way Amelia would possess Hayley was so creepy! The drama of it, though! I loved how Hayley could have just walked away (and the men of the story were encouraging her to - in order to keep her safe), not from her life and relationship or anything, but from the house because that would have protected her from Amelia.<br /><br />The love story between Harper and Hayley was so sweet as well. I've been looking forward to this one because of the friendship between the two of them. I always love the romance between friends turned lovers. Especially since both of them had been struggling to hide their feelings from one another for so long (to be fair, she had just had a baby, so it was wise of them to do so). I liked that Hayley was the first one to make a move, too (you go, girl!). But that she respected Harper enough to have him make the Big Move, since she wasn't sure how he was feeling at that point.<br /><br />And I liked how supportive Roz was of their relationship together. I know Hayley struggled with that aspect quite a bit (and I don't blame her because it must be weird to be living with your boyfriend's mom while you are dating him. Especially when you are having to describe some more intimate moments because of a ghost).</span>
