  <span id="freeText13760400580045639013" style="display:none">Red Lily was a very romantic book, but kinda freaky. The house ghost decides that she wants to invade Lily's body and Lily decides that Lily must take the ghosts place. The romance goes on between Lilly and Harper and is a wonderful love story with a two year old in the middle. I liked this one just a little bit, not as much as number one, but better than number two. It was nice to finally finish the series. I was disappointed that with all Nora Roberts research, she said that they found the Harper Bride that they were looking for in the 1890 Census. The 1890 Census was lost in a fire and only certain places remain, and the place where the woman was found was not one of those remaining places. I was very disappointed.</span>
