<span id="freeTextContainer7839482485274807997">Red Lily wraps up the amazing In the Garden series. I&apos;m still wondering how I&apos;ve not read this series before now. If you&apos;re a gardener, you&apos;ll love it. If you&apos;re partial to romance, it delivers. If you appreciate stories of family ties, deep friendships, and tradition, you&apos;ll love it. And if you enjoy a good mystery, again, it delivers. <br/><br/>To me, Red Lily is by far the creepiest of the series. Eeek! It&apos;s tense and intense, but oh, the strength of the characters and their love for each other -- beau</span>
  <span id="freeText7839482485274807997" style="display:none">Red Lily wraps up the amazing In the Garden series. I'm still wondering how I've not read this series before now. If you're a gardener, you'll love it. If you're partial to romance, it delivers. If you appreciate stories of family ties, deep friendships, and tradition, you'll love it. And if you enjoy a good mystery, again, it delivers. <br /><br />To me, Red Lily is by far the creepiest of the series. Eeek! It's tense and intense, but oh, the strength of the characters and their love for each other -- beautiful. </span>
